.SH EigValVecSym
Compute the eigenvalues and eigenvectors of a real symmetric matrix.
.SH Usage
call EigValVecSym (\f[CR]ain\f[R], \f[CR]n\f[R], \f[CR]eval\f[R],
\f[CR]evec\f[R], \f[CR]ul\f[R], \f[CR]k\f[R], \f[CR]exitstatus\f[R])
.SH Parameters
.TP
\f[CR]ain\f[R] : input, real(dp), dimension (\f[CR]n\f[R], \f[CR]n\f[R])
The input real symmetric matrix.
By default, only the upper portion of the matrix is used.
.TP
\f[CR]n\f[R] : input, integer(int32)
The rank of the matrix \f[CR]ain\f[R].
.TP
\f[CR]eval\f[R] : output, real(dp), dimension (\f[CR]k\f[R])
The eigenvalues of \f[CR]ain\f[R], sorted from largest to smallest.
.TP
\f[CR]evec\f[R] : output, real(dp), dimension (\f[CR]n\f[R], \f[CR]k\f[R])
The eigenvectors of \f[CR]ain\f[R], sorted from largest to smallest
eigenvalues.
The sign of the first element of each eigenvector is chosen to be
positive.
.TP
\f[CR]ul\f[R] : input, character, optional, default = \f[CR]U\f[R]
If \f[CR]U\f[R] then the upper portion of the matrix \f[CR]ain\f[R] will
