.SH Description
\f[CR]EigValVecSym\f[R] will calculate the eigenvalues and eigenvectors
of a real symmetric matrix.
By default, only the upper portion of the matrix is used, but this can
be changed by the optional argument \f[CR]ul\f[R].
The eigenvalues and eigenvectors are sorted from largest to smallest
eigenvalues.
If the optional parameter \f[CR]k\f[R] is specified, then only the
\f[CR]k\f[R] largest eigenvalues and their corresponding eigenvectors
will be output.
.PP
The matrix \f[CR]ain\f[R] is first factorized into a tridiagonal matrix
using the LAPACK routine \f[CR]DSYTRD\f[R], and then the eigenvalues are
calculated by calls to \f[CR]DSTEGR\f[R] and \f[CR]DORMTR\f[R].
